## 2. Universal tables

### 2.2 Atomic Node Blueprint - all tables

All business tables MUST be "Atomic"—they contain data and temporal metadata, but **zero hardcoded structural foreign keys**.

| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `[tableName]Id` | UUID/PK | Unique surrogate key for this specific record version. |
| `originatingId` | UUID | The PK of Version 1 (The "Golden Thread" identifier). |
| `previousVersionId` | UUID | The PK of the immediate predecessor (Version N-1). |
| **Business Columns** | camelCase | Domain-specific data (e.g., `projectName`, `totalBudget`). |
| `hierarchyLevel` | Integer | **(1-9)** Mandatory level indicator for context awareness. |
| `validFrom` | BigInt | Temporal start header (Unix milliseconds UTC). |
| `validTo` | BigInt | Temporal expiry header (Active = `253402300800000`). |
| `systemVersion` | Integer | Lineage Counter for **Plan B** concurrency protection. |
| `createdBy` | UUID | The `userId` of the actor who birthed this version. |
| `createdDateTime` | BigInt | Audit timestamp (Unix milliseconds UTC). |
| `sourceSystem` | String | Originating platform (e.g., "Helm", "Mobile_App"). |
| `originatingIp` | String | Network trace for security forensics. |

