## 3. Mapping (Universal Relationship Manager)

The `MAP` table is the only place where links exist. `linkToId` columns are **Strings** to allow for global URI pointers.

| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `mappingId` | UUID/PK | Unique link identifier. |
| `linkToParentId` | **String** | UUID of the "Source" (Parent Record, User, or State). |
| `linkToChildId` | **String** | UUID of the "Subject" (The record being governed). |
| `mappingContext` | String | The logic engine (e.g., `core_parent`, `state_current`). |
| `contextKey` | String | The scope: `_ROOT_` or `columnName`. |
| `sourceLocation` | String | 'LOCAL' or URI of the external database owner. |
| `validFrom` / `validTo` | BigInt | Temporal headers for the link. |
| `systemVersion` | Integer | Lineage counter. |
| `createdBy` | UUID | Audit trail. |

